A Canadian Mel brooks film with the two moose from Brother Bear. It’s a good time.
Can’t believe we watched this at my brothers twelfth birthday party. There’s a lot of human atrocity.
Is this a cult classic? Because if not I’d like to tell HBO not to list it in that category.
For me, it was the mannequin riding a hang glider through the mall, that really made this a GREAT bad film.
A little A Separate Peace and a little Dead Poets Society. A nice film to add to the “Christmas movie” canon.
Margot Robbie deserves so much better than this but it’s impossible not to smile when she’s on screen.
My friend at the end of this movie:  This is literally you’re ideal day, drinking a gin n’tonic, reading a book, smiling at your lesbian gf, while a shithead with goat for brains eats grass.
